rComments: Great Professor, very funny and helpful. Enjoy the lecture and discussion a lot.
really good prof. he warms up to you if you interact a lot and show genuine interest. got a 90 even though i expected way less.
He's alright. Readings are pretty long and also likes to give pop quizzes.

Cons: Boring to sit through lecture, higher than average course work assigned.                                                   Pros: Fair marker. Spends time helping you out during office hours. Nice and friendly guy. Would recomend taking his course, however,keep note of course work level.
I thought the lectures were great. Constant use of interesting real-world examples and his lectures were very organized.

Lectures are a pain to sit through, and people only show up during the midterm. Assignments could be a little more clear on expectations and T.A.'s mark the assignments pretty hard, good thing they're only worth 5%.

Pretty boring class and teacher, but he prepares great lecture notes. I asked a question at a TA about an assignment and she got offended and snapped at me. lol. At least they're only worth 5% apiece.
Not the most interesting course or prof, but once you get to the part with Briton, you want him back - WAY BETTER IN RETROSPECT!
BOOOOOOOOORING lectures indeed. But i suppose it is normal when teaching "economic geography". Nonetheless an interesting professor and course. Mad props and well deserved! =D
Yes he is a boring lecturer. Material is interesting espcially if you like marketing. Assignments were ok, also pretty boring. So I guess the course was ok... but just ok.

Oh GOD! The rumors are actually TRUE!  He's boring, I actually didn't expect this course to be sooo extremely economical/marketing.  Where's the geography in all this?  Darn it cause it's a full year course!  Coffee is highly recommended for class!
Soup yourself up on coffee before class because you will fall asleep.  Oh man.  The only time he looked interested in his own lecture was on the last day he was teaching us.
not a bad course..really easy if u have a eco background....too statistical...prof isnt much of a help
classes are very boring but very easy if you have an economics background
Don't expect he'll be easy on you in Statistics.  He can be your worst nightmare in exams.
